HEADWORD: Fieldwork
<hw>Field"work`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>Any temporary fortification thrown up by an army in the field; --
commonly in the plural.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All works which do not come under the head of permanent
fortification are called <qex>fieldworks</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Wilhelm.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fieldy</ent>⟦br⟧
